GameEngine

Class GameEngine

  • java.lang.Object
    • GameEngine.GameEngine

  • public class GameEngine
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the main class for handling the Game backend. This is the class that manages the backend of the game, managing serializations and de-serializations, initializing serializable instances of the players, grid and keeping track of the players' colors.
    Version:
    1.3
    Author:
    adsrc, brihijoshi

    • Constructor Detail

      • GameEngine

        public GameEngine(int _numPlayers,
                  int _gridSize)
        Parametrised constructor The _numPlayers variable speaks for itself but the _gridSize presents a catch. If _gridSize = 0, it implies a 9 x 6 grid, and if _gridSize = 1, it implies a 15 x 10 grid.
        Parameters:
        _numPlayers - Total number of players in the game
        _gridSize - An integer indicating the size of the GUI grid

      • startGame

        public void startGame()
               throws java.io.IOException,
                      java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Initialise the essential objects in case of a new game. In case the player has chosen to start a new game, i.e., the _choice option is set to 0, in this case this function initializes the essential objects like all the Player objects, the initial GameState, the Grid object, and the GameController. It also sets the first player as active and killable.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - In case their is no file to write to, or read from
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - In case there is a mis-match of classes
